{"word":"H929 - בְּהֵמָה - bᵉhêmâh - be-hay-maw' - Beast","slug":"H929","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">בְּהֵמָה</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>bᵉhêmâh"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>be-hay-maw'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Beast"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D1;&#x05BC;&#x05D4;&#x05DE;&#x05D4; - b<sup>e</sup>he&#x0302;ma&#x0302;h</b> - <i>be-hay-maw'</i><p/>From an unused root (probably meaning to be <i>mute</i>); properly a <i>dumb</i> beast; especially any large quadruped or <i>animal</i> (often collectively): - beast, cattle."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H930\">H930</a>"}]}